Research Papers

01
Natural Language Processing · Classification

Online Gambling Advertisement Detection Using OCR and IndoBERT

Automatic detection system for online gambling advertisements combining Optical Character Recognition with IndoBERT, a BERT-based model pre-trained on Indonesian text. The system extracts textual content from advertisement images and classifies them with a 95.45% F1-score on testing data — demonstrating robust performance on real-world Indonesian social media content.

IndoBERTOCRNLPText ClassificationIndonesian
02
Artificial Intelligence · Search Algorithms

Block Blast Puzzle Solver Using A* Search with Custom Admissible Heuristic

Application of the A* search algorithm to optimally solve the Block Blast puzzle game. We design a custom admissible heuristic grounded in efficient state modeling of the board, guiding the search toward maximum line-clearing moves while provably preserving optimality. The approach significantly reduces explored states compared to uninformed search baselines.

A* SearchHeuristic DesignPuzzle SolvingAI
03
Linear Algebra · Biometric Systems

Application of SVD for Fingerprint Matching in Biometric Systems

This paper applies Singular Value Decomposition to extract compact, discriminative feature representations from fingerprint images. By decomposing fingerprint matrices into their singular components, the method achieves dimensionality reduction while preserving structural identity features — enabling reliable biometric matching across variations in quality, rotation, and partial occlusion.

SVDBiometricsFingerprintLinear AlgebraPattern Recognition
04
Graph Theory · Optimization

Minimizing CCTV Units Required with Graph Coloring Using the Welsh-Powell Algorithm

We model the CCTV placement problem as a graph coloring problem, encoding spatial coverage conflicts as graph edges between camera zones. The Welsh-Powell algorithm — a greedy, degree-ordered coloring heuristic — computes the chromatic number of the conflict graph, yielding the theoretical minimum number of CCTV units needed for full area coverage without redundancy.

Graph ColoringWelsh-PowellOptimizationGraph Theory
